The paper discusses a method for predicting the performance of configurable software systems, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The method involves using spectral learning to reduce the dimensionality of the configuration space, which could also be considered a topic in programming languages (cs.PL). The use of predictive models and optimization techniques also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the focus on performance optimization could be relevant to systems and control (cs.SY).
